Issue Description: 

Highlights of Discovery Channel India magazine, May 2014
In DCM this May, discover the intricacies of human brain and why humans love to Live by Lists. Get an insight into your obsession about ticking items on to-do-lists and find out that you are not the only one. 
The Chinese have dominated most spheres of life, and now it is the turn of Chinese Art. Making big international news, contemporary Chinese art is the new talk in art world. Hear from the Masters what they have to say about the New 'Chineseness'. In an industry where the stakes are high can crime be far behind. Find out about the murky world of fakes and forgery in art in Crime in Creativity. For wildlife enthusiasts Locking Horns brings into focus the state of rhinos in South Africa and what the future holds for them. Get under the skin of master evader, ex-US Navy Seal as he talks about Extreme Survival and being chased by six of the best armies of the world.

All this and more hair-raising information in the May issue of Discovery Channel Magazine India
 
Magazine Description: 

Discovery Channel Magazine India, published by the India Today Group, is a monthly magazine boasting premium content based on original and in-depth left-field research. Featuring world-class photography and infographics, the stories are presented with a good dose of humour, insight and attitude, making the eclectic range of topics, from history and mathematics to forensics and gaming, immediately accessible to readers.
